pgTitle: List of mountains and hills of the Eifel

rows.text: Highest point of the Schneifel ridge and hence the Schnee Eifel
Highest mountain in Belgium and the Hohes Venn
Highest mountain of the Zitter Forest and in North Rhine-Westphalia west of the Rhine; second highest mountain in Belgium; site of observation tower on the (German) eastern slopes of the mountain
Highest mountain in the district of Aachen
Highest mountain of the Pelmer Forest, site of wooden observation post
Highest hill on the edge of the Prümer Kalkmulde
Site of the old NATO direction-finding station, an observation tower and a telecommunication tower; Nearby: fire lookout tower
Highest elevation of the Meulenwald; site of Kellerberg observation tower
Has the steepest individual vineyard in Europe
Site of Krausberg Tower and Krausberghütte
Site of partly accessible quarry and Roman ringwork
